    <vamendmenttexta />
        <blockquote>
        <h3>Choice 2: Enhance seconders to Q [3:1]</h3>
	<p>General Resolutions are an important framework within the Debian
	Project. Yet, in a project the size of Debian, the current requirements
	to initiate one are too small.

	<p>Therefore the Debian project resolves that
	<ol type=a>
	<li> The constitution gets changed to not require K developers to sponsor
	a resolution, but floor(Q). [see &sect;4.2(1)]</li>
	<li>Delaying a decision of a Delegate or the DPL [&sect;4.2(2.2)],
	as well as resolutions against a shortening of discussion/voting
	period or to overwrite a TC decision [&sect;4.2(2.3)] requires floor(Q)
	developers to sponsor the resolution.</li>
	<li> the definition of K gets erased from the constitution. [&sect;4.2(7)]</li>
	</ol>
	<p>(Numbers in brackets are references to sections in the constitution).
        </blockquote>
